xbase
------------------------------------------
XBase is an xbase (i.e. dBase, FoxPro, etc.) compatible C++ class
library originally by Gary Kunkel and others.

XBASE is useful for accessing data in legacy dBase 3 and 4 database
files as well as a general light-weight database engine.  It includes
support for DBF (dBase version 3 and 4) data files, NDX and NTX indexes,
and DBT (dBase version 3 and 4).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15

Build requirements:
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.4-1.4p6-4
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.0-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gcc-g++-3.4.4-3
  kapptemplate-3.5.9-1
  libtool-2.2.2-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://linux.techass.com/projects/xdb/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/xdb/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack xbase-2.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./xbase-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libxbase-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libxbase2.0-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xbase-2.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xbase-2.0.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

